### Describe the Bug

On the current page with hash, if click `a` tag generated by next/link without hash on the same page, the URL will be changed to the one without hash, but the page will not be scrolled to the top. (e.g. URL: `/foo#section` -> `/foo`)
And if click again, the URL remains the same, but the page scrolls to the top.

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45661101/147846512-9908ae59-dec8-4ba4-b8bb-b9fe7ccd35c9.mov

In order to scroll to the top on the first click, embed the following in the page component.

```ts
  const router = useRouter();
  useEffect(() => {
    router.events.on("hashChangeComplete", (path: string) => {
      if (!path.includes("#")) {
        window.scrollTo(0, 0);
      }
    });
  }, [router.events]);
```

However, I would like the library (Next Router) to handle the scrolling properly.

https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/v12.0.7/packages/next/shared/lib/router/router.ts#L1610

```diff
  scrollToHash(as: string): void {
    const [, hash] = as.split('#')
    // Scroll to top if the hash is just `#` with no value or `#top`
    // To mirror browsers
-   if (hash === '' || hash === 'top') {
+   if (hash === undefined || hash === '' || hash === 'top') {
      window.scrollTo(0, 0)
      return
    }
```

### Expected Behavior

The page should be scrolled to the top when the first click (navigation).

### To Reproduce

1. Clone the following repository
2. Run `next dev` or `next build` & `next start`

https://github.com/swallowtail62/next-link-inspection

Or simply use next/link with hash and next/link without hash on the same page.

