### Describe the Bug

Hi,

I am facing a similar issue reported in other tickets where the but could not find a solution and to be honest understand what the problem is. 

The issue is: In _app.js I am wrapping meta tags inside next/head but they gets rendered only client-side. The rest is rendered statically.

_app.js is a class react component with getInitialProps, and we are rendering statically with `next build && next export`. 

I also thought getInitialProps might not be the right one to use?  but In a separated clean react project I tried to replicate this setup (class + getInitialProps) and works fine the head is rendered statically too, but not in the project I am working on. So must be something else... ?

**A snippet of _app.tsx.**

```js
export default class MyApp extends App<Props, State> {

  ...LOGIC

  static async getInitialProps({Component, ctx}: AppContext) {
    let pageProps = {};
    if (Component.getInitialProps) {
      pageProps = await Component.getInitialProps(ctx);
    }
    return {path: ctx.asPath, pageProps};
  }

...LOGIC

render() {

    const {Component, pageProps, path} = this.props;
    const {theme, themeMode} = this.state as State;
    
    const handlers = [
      instrumentationHandlers.createConsoleHandler(),
      instrumentationHandlers.createTealiumHandler(),
    ];

    return (
      <>
        <Head>
          <title key='title'>TITLE</title>
          <meta
            key="description"
            name="description"
            content="DESCRIPTION"
          />
        </Head>
        <InstrumentationProvider
          {...createEventInstrumentation(handlers, {
            ...pageProps,
          })}
        >
          <ThemeProvider theme={theme}>
            <ThemeMode.Provider value={themeMode}>
              <Global
                styles={css`
                  html {
                    scroll-behavior: smooth;
                    scroll-padding-top: 90px;
                  }
                  @font-face {
                    font-family: 'DM Sans';
                    src: url('static/fonts/dmsans-regular-webfont.woff2')
                        format('woff2'),
                      url('static/fonts/dmsans-regular-webfont.woff')
                        format('woff');
                    font-style: normal;
                    font-weight: 400;
                    font-display: swap;
                  }
                  
              />

              <PageLoadInstrumentation />
              <Component
                {...pageProps}
                path={path}
                toggleTheme={this.toggleTheme}
                themeMode={themeMode}
              />
            </ThemeMode.Provider>
          </ThemeProvider>
        </InstrumentationProvider>
      </>
    );
  }
}
```


Rendering Head in _document.TSX works, it makes the Head statically rendered but I want it to be dynamic. So different for every page and. So ideally would like to have it in _app.tsx

**Other Things I tried:** 

We are also using Helmet in _document.js but commenting it out still, _app.js is rendered client-side.

Commenting everything apart from the meta tags in _app.js still is rendered CS


Thank you,


