A package gets inlined twice instead of once. This only happens in `_middleware`, not in pages.

Happens with `npm run dev` and on `npm run build`.

I would expect the package to only get inlined once.

Having the package around twice leads to further bugs, like when a module exports a setter and a getter and the consumers happen to use two separate instances of that module. The getters never see the values set by the setter if it's not the same instance.

