### Describe the Bug

  In the project we're using `Next-Auth` and in `_app.tsx` we have `getInitialProps` where we're fetching the session and some other stuff.
Now `index` has `getStaticProps`, which ideally should help with performance, since we have a lot of API calls and having them prefetched on the server would increase performance quite substantially. Issue is - that information should be seen only by authenticated users.

**ISSUE:** `index` page with `getStaticProps` generates a static page with cached user data which can be sensitive data as well.
**Example:**
1st user logs in and is not able to see authenticated status or information meant for authenticated user until `revalidate` period ends. After that - authenticated status is visible if page is refreshed.
2nd user (in this case new private tab or another browser) is immediately authenticated as 1st user. When refreshing after `revalidate` period has ended - user is not authenticated anymore.
After all this 1st user would be unauthenticated until the next `revalidate` period...Rinse and repeat :) 


![next auth getstaticprops](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70571729/153834861-654a6e35-5a5c-45d2-8f0e-dea4ea68e2ca.gif)


