### Describe the Bug

Currently, I have an issue where if calling `router.push` is book-ended by calls to `router.replace` with `shallow: true`, it will stop `getServerSideProps` being called, causing the URL to update in the browser but the content of the page doesn't change.

### Expected Behavior

If I navigate to a page using push and shallow:false, I would expect `getServerSideProps` to always be called when going back. 

### To Reproduce

Here is the example I'm using currently to re-produce this issue:

If you're using the basic next template
```
npx create-next-app nextjs-blog --use-npm --example "https://github.com/vercel/next-learn/tree/master/basics/learn-starter"
```

Just add this to pages/post/[...slug].js

```
import router from 'next/router';
import Link from 'next/link';
import React, { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react';

export const getServerSideProps = (ctx) => {
  console.log('getServerSideProps', ctx.query);
  return {
    props: {
      page: ctx.query.slug[0],
    },
  };
};

const Post = (props) => {
  const [index, setIndex] = useState(0);

  const handleClick = () => {
    setIndex(index + 1);

    router.replace(`/post/${props.page}/clicks/${index + 1}`, undefined, {
      shallow: true,
    });
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    setIndex(0);
  }, [props.page]);

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>This is post {props.page}</h1>

      <h3>Clicks {index}</h3>

      <button onClick={handleClick}>bump</button>

      <Link href="/post/1" passHref>
        <a>
          Post 1
        </a>
      </Link>

      <Link href="/post/2" passHref>
        <a>
          Post 2
        </a>
      </Link>

      <Link href="/post/3" passHref>
        <a>
          Post 3
        </a>
      </Link>
    </div>
  )
};

export default Post;
```

To re-produce the normal behavior, click bump a couple of times, click another page link and click back. This will update the heading tag and call getServerSideProps each time `router.push` or history back is used. 

![Artboard](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2168465/154044614-758aadaf-1367-4cd7-affc-ccc6a0ec2c4a.png)

The unexpected behavior comes if you click bump a couple of times, click another page link, click bump a couple more times and then click back. The heading will update when `router.push` is called, but after history back `getServerSideProps` will not be called. Therefore although the URL changes, the content of the page doesn't. 

![Artboard2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2168465/154044641-573d80f2-dc09-4ec0-ae8c-76cfd21fe56b.png)

