### Describe the Bug

**Headers, and perhaps other `Request` configuration is not sent with `fetch(Request)` in vercel prod.**

For consistent behaviour the `fetch` `init` param must be used.

i.e

```
  const req = new NextRequest("https://some-endpoint.com/", {
    headers: {
      "some-header": "foo=bar",
    },
  });
  
  // request will not have the custom header `some-header`
  await fetch(req);
  
  // request will have the custom header
  await fetch(req.url.toString(), req)
```

According to the spec a Request should be a valid first param, and that can include headers https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#concept-request https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/fetch

Indeed the behaves as expected locally with `next dev` or `vercel dev`

