### Describe the feature you'd like to request

# Nested sub route component handling
Sometimes we may have a sub route (`/dashboard/xxx`) of a parent route (`/dashboard`) which all use the layout that the parent route use, but because nextjs only render the specific file for the specific route, we can only extract the dashboard layout to some where(like `/components`) like below:
```tsx
// ./pages/dashboard/edit.tsx

// for /dashboard/edit
function DashboardEdit() {
    return <DashboardLayout >...<DashboardLayout  />
}

// ./pages/dashboard/setting.tsx

// for /dashboard/setting
function DashboardSetting() {
    return <DashboardLayout >...<DashboardLayout  />
}

// ./pages/dashboard/index.tsx

// for /dashboard
function Dashboard() {
    return <DashboardLayout />
}

// ./components/DashboardLayout.tsx

function DashboardLayout({children}) {
    return (
        <xxx>
           ...
           {children || <p>What you want to do?</p>}
           ...
       </xxx>
    )
}
```
It's fine with just few sub routes, but once you increasing the amount of sub route, the thing starts become complicated since you will need to manually import the Dashboard Layout every time you create a new sub route, it will become even more worse if you have deep nested route or sub route of sub route
(using the method that suggested in [nextjs docs](https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/layouts#per-page-layouts) will not actually help us since we still need import the layout everytime to use the component inside the getLayout function)

